Subject: Derived Periphery Correlation Worker Latch Source

Description: Preserved derived source for the periphery_correlation_014 worker latch observed during LM Studio corpus benchmarking.

& [DerivedPeripheryCorrelationWorkerLatchSource] is preserved derived source
  + [source_type] is derived_from_benchmark_observation
  + [observed_subject] is corpus_periphery_correlation_014
  + [initial_failure] is worker produced a plausible correlation scan but omitted the literal required term hypothesis from field values
  + [retry_001_failure] is worker included required terms but removed the two-space property-line prefix and failed raw SOP format
  + [accepted_retry] is retry 002 passed after the prompt emphasized literal hypothesis and exact two-space property-line prefixes
  + [derived_latches] is hypothesis_literal_value_latch, property_line_prefix_latch, causation_boundary_latch, and ASCII stability check
  + [reason_for_change] is associative scan tasks need both semantic caution around causation and exact raw SOP line structure before worker output can become readiness evidence
  + [outside] is hidden model state, broad LM Studio competence, project-root authority, worker mutation authority, credentials, destructive action, certain causation without evidence, and untested integration_disposition family

  = must: preserve failed attempts as benchmark data
  = must: treat retry success as one family signal only
  = must: keep Codex as validator and integration authority
  - never: treat correlation language as causation proof
